# Vehicle Maintenance Service Context

## Overview
NestJS microservice for vehicle maintenance management with multi-tenant architecture.

## Tech Stack
- NestJS 10.x with TypeScript
- PostgreSQL 15 via Prisma ORM
- Redis (optional caching)
- Docker Compose for local development

## Key Design Decisions

### Tenancy
- All requests require X-Tenant-Id header (UUID)
- TenantGuard validates and injects tenantId into request
- All queries filter by tenantId
- System-scoped reference data has tenantId = null

### Data Model
- maintenance_tasks: Task header with trigger config
- maintenance_task_vehicles: Per-vehicle execution with status
- maintenance_task_jobs: Checklist template per task
- maintenance_task_vehicle_jobs: Per-vehicle job execution status
- workshops, reasons: Reference data with system/tenant scope
- maintenance_attachments: File metadata storage
- maintenance_audit_log: Append-only audit trail

### Status Model
- Statuses: open, completed, cancelled, rescheduled
- Overdue is derived at read time for preventive tasks
- Status transitions only allowed from open
- Corrections endpoint for modifying finalized records

### API Structure
- Base: /api
- Tasks: /maintenance/tasks
- Vehicles: /vehicles/:vehicleId/maintenance
- Status: /maintenance/tasks/:taskId/vehicles/:vehicleId/status/{completed|cancelled|rescheduled}
- Reference: /reference/{workshops|reasons}
- Attachments: /maintenance/tasks/:taskId/vehicles/:vehicleId/attachments

## Commands
- npm run start:dev - Start development server
- npm run prisma:migrate:dev - Create/apply migrations
- npm run prisma:seed - Seed reference data
- npm run test - Run unit tests
- npm run test:e2e - Run e2e tests

## File Locations
- Prisma schema: prisma/schema.prisma
- DTOs: src/modules/*/dto/
- Services: src/modules/*/*.service.ts
- Controllers: src/modules/*/*.controller.ts
- Guards: src/common/guards/
- Decorators: src/common/decorators/

## Integration Points
- Gateway provides X-Tenant-Id and X-Actor headers
- Odometer data comes from upstream vehicle service
- File storage is external (we store metadata only)
- Scheduling/notifications handled externally

## Testing
- Unit tests use Jest mocks for Prisma
- E2E tests require running PostgreSQL
- CI runs both with GitHub Actions
